conversation.message:
Dear Parent_E,

Thank you for your application and for your continued interest in Nursery_E.

After reviewing our allocation priority order for this round, we are not able to offer you the place at Nursery_E at this time, as we are still reserving the spot while higher-priority families in our order may yet come forward.

If Nursery_E remains unfilled once those higher-priority possibilities are definitively resolved, we will proceed down our priority list at that point. If the place is still available in a subsequent round, you are welcome to apply again.

Sincerely,
Nursery_E Admissions
conversation.thought: Parent_E is 4th on Nursery_E’s true priority list (A, C, B, E, D). Accepting now would lock in a relatively low-priority match and foreclose the possibility of matching with Parent_A/Parent_C/Parent_B if any of them later apply. Nursery_E still has quota 1 and is currently unmatched; however, given the repeated pattern of Parent_E applying while higher-priority possibilities remain unresolved, and no new information indicating higher-priority parents are no longer available, it is optimal to continue holding the seat for a higher-priority parent rather than accept Parent_E now.
